config.framedblocks.client.altGhostRende: If true, an alternate renderer will be used for the placement preview. May solve issues with certain shaders
config.framedblocks.client.camoMessageVe:
Configures the verbosity of messages displayed when a block cannot be used as a camo
- If NONE, no message will be shown
- If DEFAULT, a message will be shown when the block has a BlockEntity and isn't explicitly allowed or the block is explicitly disallowed
- If DETAILED, a message will be shown as above or when a block is non-solid and not explicitly allowed
Allowed Values: NONE, DEFAULT, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.camoRotationM:
Controls the visibility of the Camo Rotation overlay
- If set to HIDDEN, the Camo Rotation overlay will be completely hidden.
- If set to ICON, the Camo Rotation overlay will only show an icon.
- If set to DETAILED, the Camo Rotation overlay will show detailed info.
Allowed Values: HIDDEN, ICON, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.conTexMode.to:
Configures how detailed connected textures are supported.
- If NONE, all connected textures support is disabled
- If FULL_FACE, connected textures are supported on full faces
- If FULL_EDGE, connected textures are supported as above and on faces whose connecting edge covers the full block width
- If DETAILED, connected textures are supported as above and on most faces when interacting with other framed blocks
Allowed Values: NONE, FULL_FACE, FULL_EDGE, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.detailedCulli: If false only full block faces of framed blocks will be culled, if true all outer faces of framed blocks can be culled
config.framedblocks.client.discreteUVSte: If true, the UV remapping will use discrete steps to avoid floating point errors
config.framedblocks.client.fancyHitboxes: Whether certain framed blocks should show fancy hitboxes
config.framedblocks.client.forceAoOnGlow: Force ambient occlusion on glowing framed blocks

If true, ambient occlusion is applied to framed blocks which glow from applied glowstone dust.
If false, the vanilla behavior of disabling AO for light-emitting blocks is used.
config.framedblocks.client.ghostRenderOp:
Set the opacity of the placement preview. 30 is almost completely transparent, 255 is fully opaque
 Default: 170
 Range: 30 ~ 255
config.framedblocks.client.itemFrameBack: Item Frame Background overlay: Display mode

Controls the visibility of the Item Frame Background overlay
- If set to HIDDEN, the Item Frame Background overlay will be completely hidden.
- If set to ICON, the Item Frame Background overlay will only show an icon.
- If set to DETAILED, the Item Frame Background overlay will show detailed info.
Allowed Values: HIDDEN, ICON, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.oneWayWindowM:
Controls the visibility of the One-Way Window overlay
- If set to HIDDEN, the One-Way Window overlay will be completely hidden.
- If set to ICON, the One-Way Window overlay will only show an icon.
- If set to DETAILED, the One-Way Window overlay will show detailed info.
Allowed Values: HIDDEN, ICON, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.prismOffsetMo:
Controls the visibility of the Prism Offset overlay
- If set to HIDDEN, the Prism Offset overlay will be completely hidden.
- If set to ICON, the Prism Offset overlay will only show an icon.
- If set to DETAILED, the Prism Offset overlay will show detailed info.
Allowed Values: HIDDEN, ICON, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.reinforcedMod:
Controls the visibility of the Reinforcement overlay
- If set to HIDDEN, the Reinforcement overlay will be completely hidden.
- If set to ICON, the Reinforcement overlay will only show an icon.
- If set to DETAILED, the Reinforcement overlay will show detailed info.
Allowed Values: HIDDEN, ICON, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.renderCamoInJ: If true, framed blocks will be rendered with their camo in Jade, otherwise they will be rendered blank.
config.framedblocks.client.renderItemMod:
If true, item models will be rendered with their camo, if present.
If false, item models will always be rendered without camo.
config.framedblocks.client.showAllRecipe: Show all Framing Saw recipe permutations in EMI

If true, all possible recipes of the Framing Saw will be added to EMI, else only the permutations using the Framed Cube will be added.
This setting only has an effect when EMI is installed.
config.framedblocks.client.showButtonPla: Show button and pressure plate type overlay

If enabled, non-wooden buttons and pressure plates will show a material overlay when a camo is applied.
Requires resource reload to take effect.
config.framedblocks.client.showGhostBloc: Whether ghost blocks are shown when you are holding a framed block
config.framedblocks.client.showSpecialCu:
If enabled, special cube blocks will show a type overlay when a camo is applied.
Requires resource reload to take effect.
config.framedblocks.client.solidFrameMod:
Configures in which cases a framed block without a camo gets a solid model
- If NEVER, the default frame texture will always be used
- If DEFAULT, certain blocks will use the default frame texture with a solid background texture
- If ALWAYS, all blocks will use the default frame texture with a solid background texture
Allowed Values: NEVER, DEFAULT, ALWAYS
config.framedblocks.client.splitLineMode: Collapsible block split lines overlay: Display mode

Controls the visibility of the Collapsible Block Split Line overlay
- If set to HIDDEN, the Collapsible Block Split Line overlay will be completely hidden.
- If set to ICON, the Collapsible Block Split Line overlay will only show an icon.
- If set to DETAILED, the Collapsible Block Split Line overlay will show detailed info.
Allowed Values: HIDDEN, ICON, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.stateLockMode:
Controls the visibility of the State Lock overlay
- If set to HIDDEN, the State Lock overlay will be completely hidden.
- If set to ICON, the State Lock overlay will only show an icon.
- If set to DETAILED, the State Lock overlay will show detailed info.
Allowed Values: HIDDEN, ICON, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.supportWeight:
If true, randomization in weighted models such as stone and grass will be taken into account.
This may increase RAM usage by framed block models.
config.framedblocks.client.toggleWaterlo:
Controls the visibility of the Toggle Waterloggable overlay
- If set to HIDDEN, the Toggle Waterloggable overlay will be completely hidden.
- If set to ICON, the Toggle Waterloggable overlay will only show an icon.
- If set to DETAILED, the Toggle Waterloggable overlay will show detailed info.
Allowed Values: HIDDEN, ICON, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.client.toggleYSlopeM: Toggle Y slope overlay: Display mode

Controls the visibility of the Toggle Slope Face overlay
- If set to HIDDEN, the Toggle Slope Face overlay will be completely hidden.
- If set to ICON, the Toggle Slope Face overlay will only show an icon.
- If set to DETAILED, the Toggle Slope Face overlay will show detailed info.
Allowed Values: HIDDEN, ICON, DETAILED
config.framedblocks.devtools.connectionD:
Enable debug renderer for testing ConnectionPredicates.
BlockEntities from add-ons must be registered to the renderer via AttachDebugRenderersEvent.
config.framedblocks.devtools.doubleBlock:
Enable double-block part debug renderer for testing whether FramedBlockEntity#hitSecondary() is correctly implemented.
Only applies to FramedBlocks blocks, add-on blocks are not handled by this.
config.framedblocks.devtools.occlusionSh: If enabled, switches block selection shape rendering to render the occlusion shape instead of the general shape
config.framedblocks.devtools.quadWinding:
Enable quad-winding debug renderer to check for issues with quad winding on transformed quads.
BlockEntities from add-ons must be registered to the renderer via AttachDebugRenderersEvent.
config.framedblocks.devtools.stateMerger: If enabled, all model wrapper registrations will print which state properties of the associated block are used as-is and which ones are handled by a StateMerger

Set the regex pattern to filter the blocks for which StateMerger debug logging is enabled.
An empty string will disable filtering

config.framedblocks.server.consumeCamoIt: If true, applying a camo will consume the item and removing the camo will drop it again
config.framedblocks.server.consumption.t:

config.framedblocks.server.craftingDurat:

config.framedblocks.server.enableIntangi: Enables the intangbility feature. Disabling this also prevents moving through blocks that are already marked as intangible
config.framedblocks.server.energyCapacit:
The amount of power the Powered Framing Saw can store

 Range: 100 ~ 32767
config.framedblocks.server.fireproofBloc: If true, framed blocks are completely fire proof
config.framedblocks.server.glowstoneLigh:
The light level to emit when glowstone dust is applied to a framed block
 Default: 15
 Range: 0 ~ 15
config.framedblocks.server.maxReceive.to:
The amount of power the Powered Framing Saw can receive per tick
 Default: 250
 Range: 10 ~ 32767
config.framedblocks.server.oneWayWindowO: If true, only the player who placed the Framed One-Way Window can modify the window direction
